Flash News | yukrix Exposed Again, Exploits On Alt | ---------------------- yukrix is back in the news again and for all the wrong reasons. After his ban in-game, he’s been claiming that he hasn't been playing The Wild West on an alternate account, but evidence uncovered the other day showed otherwise. In a raid launched by Coco Pops ,a user named "Misora7" was hitting all headshots, very similarly to Yukrix before he was banned. Hitting the amount of consecutive headshots that Yukrix hits are pretty much impossible, no matter how much experience or skill you have. Taking a closer look at Misora7's Roblox account, despite having one changed username, he appears to be an alternate account. He only has a few friends, most of whom don't even play Wild West, and is only in a few roblox groups. In leaked DMs with Patrick and Yukrix, Yukrix confirmed that he was in-game at the same time Misora7 was. Overall, it certainly looks like Yukrix was exploiting on an alternate account. The Western Weekly #flash-news BOT 10-Aug-21 05:43 PM
Flash News: Darth retires from Western Weekly Yesterday, some major changes in leadership happened in Western Weekly. Darth, server manager of Western Weekly for the past few months, announced his retirement. In his retirement message, he thanked most of WW's staff for all they've done for WW, as well as thanking a few of his friends. Also included in this message was some honorable mentions, which included Coco Pops, Pinkerton Private Eye Agency, Neo Pollos Hermanos and The Corleone Empire. The dishonorable mentions included Frontier Militia, Outcast, Voltage, Cartel De Zelus, and "Anything related to Kingsman and/or Ass Hats Clan". This certainly is a big change for Western Weekly, but the former leader, and founder, Smusher, has retaken her leadership position in Western Weekly. It's certainly is sad to see such a valued staff member of Western Weekly go, but Hopefully WW will have a bright future. Wild West Guidelines/Rules updated Yesterday, the official Wild West Guidelines/Rules were updated. A new section was added, called "Factions". This new section now made it possible to be banned from The Wild West for actions on discord and other platforms. The new rules prohibited: Doxxing, harassment, hate speech, threats and others. We've already seen players get banned for actions outside of TWW, such as Cartel De Zelus, after they sold child porn. The new section also added the possibility of your in-game faction getting deleted, if the leader of said faction fails to abide those rules. A few hours after the guidelines were updated, CDZ's in-game faction was deleted once again. Due to these new guidelines, many in-game factions will probably be deleted. Written by: @dwn dog

TWW Championships Starts! Yesterday TWW Championships was announced, Eight teams of three go head to head in two mini-games that have been made to test your Wild West skills like parkour, combat, teamwork and more. At the end of the tournament, the top two teams with the most points will go up against one another in one final game to decide the ultimate champion. They will receive the grand prize of a full Skeleton Horse Set + 30 Thunderstruck Logs. can you be the ultimate champion? Join and find out: https://discord.gg/2fyPhSx7 Spitfire Nerf Sky has announced recently that the Spitfire Revolving Sniper has FINALLY been nerfed-ish for (hopefully) the last time. In the first rendition, the Spitfire had about a 3.5 second reload speed which was quickly nerfed to have the reload be longer. Many players complained about how overpowered the Spitfire was even though it has a relatively long reload. The weapon now deals more longer the farther away your opponent is, it deals 20 to the body and 100 to the head at close range which rises the farther away your opponent is, capping out at 100 body damage and 300 head-shot damage. It's extremely powerful at long range now, rather than being extremely powerful whenever. More information on this gun can be found here : https://thewild-west.fandom.com/wiki/Spitfire_Revolving_Sniper https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/776507736841650176/883343464778039306/unknown.png |Other News| -Sweaty Rats lost to Serenity in a friendly war. -The Corleone Empire and Neo Pollos Hermanos fought Night Hawk Militia and The Empire and won -Frontier Militia had a war with Nordic Atlantic Treaty Organisation which resulted in a tie due to server crash. https://streamable.com/b39341 -Frontier Militia and some Outcast members fought Nordic Atlantic Treaty Organisation and Cartel De Zelus and won. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=swuqpiMD6-U -Unity and Cartel De Zelus had a war resulting in a win for Unity -Rogue Wolves hit 300 members in their discord -Cartel De Zelus server got raided -Valiant fought cartel de zelus and won -Serenity and valiant unallied -TCE fought BF in a friendly war and won. https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/735915937600897054/884102713611255868/image1.png https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VlBvmGY5Xg8&ab_channel=Xelite @Flash News Ping Make sure to join the Western Weekly! https://discord.gg/dn9BE3QksT (edited)

Merge W/ KM? | ---------------------- This Corleone-Blue Ridge Federation War is heating up by the day, and this is another new development, and certainly not a good one for TBRF. In reality, Fat was in full control of his account the full time and posted these links as some sort of attempt at comedy. This though did not go over very well with his members or even HRs. In the screenshots below, you can see that council member Leojsufur left the server, Legolas, co-leader of BF, was demoted, and “danns mad; ties mad; rex is mad” all of which are HRs. Many members said that BF was “turning into a worse community everyday” and Legolas proclaiming “we are turning into OC man”. Legolas also said “i think this is the part where we merge with KM”. Fat was very nonchalant about the whole matter, cracking jokes in chat. Fat to his credit, had some sense knocked into him and apologized for what he did and has promised to make things better. Though it should be noted that Tielupz, co-leader of BF, said “yea stop sending pron [porn] to 8 year old girls”. Usually this could be written off as satire however knowing Fat and him making very sick jokes, it should be noted. We’ll see if BF merges with KM or things turn around but this is not a pretty look for BF and the coalition.

| SBS Makes Announcement, No Date on Building | ---------------------- Starboard Studios released a developer blog today, giving their players a long awaited update on the, well, update. Anyhow, Kaz, who wrote the post, did not mention two key developers, those being Tamara and Tyridge. Although concerning, Kaz did announce level progression, a revamp of the current and outdated Quest system in the game. The system works like many other progression systems in game and even provides perks for PvP combat (not much though). We also got word when the next update will be coming out, that being the annual Halloween Update! This update will not come with building, drawing the ire of many players but will come with Progression. Furthermore, SBS announced that they have delayed The Wild Seas, a game slated to be released this past summer but inevitably. The game will be released in 2022. Before the end of the post, Kaz posted ONE screenshot of Building with the caption “Building coming along nicely”. Flash News | Halloween Update Dropped, Building Delayed! | ---------------------- The Wild West recently received a fresh, new Halloween update. The update comes with a lot of new things that we've never seen in previous updates such as: • UFOs that appear every hour. They drop a very OP laser gun that does 60 damage and deals AOE damage (Area of Effect). • NPC skeletons made their first appearance in places such as Tribal Village, Highlands, Great Desert mines. • A new "cursed" volcanic pistol obtained from killing the boss. • A Wendigo horse that's immune to headshot multiplier. • A Halloween Skeleton Boss to defeat in The Underworld. • The Underworld can be opened through a gate behind the waterfalls between Howling Peak and Buffalo Ridge. You will need 30 bones in order to access the Under World portal. • A new skull lantern. • A Ceremonial Dagger that makes you run faster once you have it equipped and on hands. •And a whole lot more (details in #deleted-channel , more will come soon) For TWW Halloween OGs, there's still the classic wendigo spawning every time the moon rises. We won’t really tell you guys how to complete everything as this could ruin the fun and adventure. However we will give you this very useful map. Some people expected the building update to also drop since the devs posted sneak peeks mixed with the Halloween update and the building one. How long will players still wait for the promised May 2020 update? Anyways, the developers confirmed that since they were late for the Halloween update, it will remain for the whole month of November. Unfortunately, no building came in this update as Kaz previously announced, however the update is being received positively by the community and will hopefully keep us occupied until then. | Artheus Retires! | ---------------------- Artheus, formerly Community Manager of Starboard Studios, has retired from his position. Artheus, who’s been in the community for over 3 years, said that the decision was his own and he just wanted to move on and do other things in life. Artheus has had a long and controversial history in the factions community, from him banning United Factions back in Early 2020 to playing a hand in the purging of factions in 2020 to being generally hated for his moderation practices, we wish Artheus the best in all of his future endeavors. | KM-BF Merger: Not Meant To Be | ---------------------- Last week, Kingsmen merged into Bleeding Falcons, a decision not popular with many people inside Kingsmen who more liked the community side of KM. Many moved to Serenity, but more on that later. Fact of the matter is, the decision was controversial at best inside KM with Yeetius, founder of TBRF, agreeing that FarWest did ‘fuck up’. Members who disagreed with the decision fled Kingsmen for the newly revived Serenity, founded by Desired and Addie, the former owners. Well now FarWest seems to be pulling out while he still can with him leaving over Legolas and him “starting fights with SEN for no good reason”. He also mentioned the “racism, homophobia, gore, etc.” in BF. He didn’t say if KM was going to remain in the TWW community, but let his members stay in BF if they wanted to. The fate of Kingsmen remains in limbo as of now. Will they disband? Will they reform? Time will ultimately tell. | Where is TBRF? | ------------------------ The Blue Ridge Federation has seemingly fallen off the face of the earth for the past few weeks. Meanwhile hostilities between The Corleone Empire, TBRF’s sworn enemy, and Bleeding Falcons, faction in TBRF, have died down. From this day forward, we will look at bans with far more scrutiny. Once again, we are sorry. (edited)

The Western Weekly #flash-news BOT 21-Dec-21 08:01 PM
| SBS Ends Scamming Rampage | ---------------------- Starboard Studios is finally responding to the scamming crisis in The Wild West following the update where they re-added dropping auction items into the game. Sky went out in a statement and called the re-adding of dropping auction items a “mistake” and stating that if you have proof of being scamming, you are eligible to receive some compensation if you send it in to a Community Manager. But this however has been discontinued likely due to the amount of time and effort needed to confirm scams. The ability to drop auction items has been removed from the game. In another statement, she said that they’re going to “try provide a basic trading system when we release our Christmas update” and that this new system would record all trades. Sneak Peaks of the trading system have been shown, with the first one only allowing 4 slots for trading and the second one having 6 slots for trading due to demand. There also seems to be a "fee" which is basically taxes. The amount you get taxed seems to be related to the value of the item in the trade. This comes after hundreds upon hundreds of scams done by players. Now that the dust has settled, at least some members of the community have shown their true colors and how some people would rather be greedy and take for themselves rather than doing it the honest way. https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/478996456766963723/919763785684758528/TradeSurchargeExampleBeta.mp4

Flash News | Western Triad II | --------------------- The Western Triad, likely one of the most recognizable faction names of all time, is coming back. Disbanding in February of 2021, it is being revived with 3 main factions: • Bleeding Falcons - Indian Gamers merged into BF - United Gaming Gaming Cartel merged into BF • Kingsmen Some of you may wonder why this is important. Some history: The Western Triad was formed in October of 2020 as a merger between Ass Hats Clan, Indian Gamers, and Bleeding Falcons after their victory in the TAF I-TFE War. WT went on to fight Kingsmen, FarWest’s faction (ironic he’s leading WT now), Cartel De Familia, owned by Lyca, and all of TAF II. It was known as the most powerful faction and their leader Yeetius being seen as a de facto community leader. After it disbanded in February of 2021, two of WT’s main players were exposed for exploiting: AdamZombieKiller and Yukrix, which has caused some to call their success a lie. Their enemies are the same as before the factions all merged, those being: • The Corleone Empire & it’s allies • Lotus & it’s allies Something that should be noted: Kingsmen and Bleeding Falcons tried to merge once before but it failed due to differences between FarWest and Fat. However, with new BF leadership and Kevin coming into the scene, there is a better chance of this sticking. We’ll see if this faction become a new powerhouse in the community.

The Western Weekly #flash-news BOT 10-Feb-22 01:56 PM
Flash News | Update on SBS Partnership System and Game Decline | --------------------- A while ago, Starboard Studios announced a new partnership system, replacing their recruitment channel. To apply for a partnership, you need to have at least 250 members, and 55 active ones, meaning most factions are unable to apply and recruit new members. So far there has been 7 partnerships: The Marketplace, The Western Trading Hub, Hunt and Trade, Bronze City Books, Fre_nzy's Lounge, MIDI Plaza, and leadCarl Community. Aside from those ones, many large organisations have been blacklisted or are just unable to apply, such as Western Weekly, Western Times, Western Vision, Western Land Co, and other servers. Servers unable to partner have had to find alternate ways to advertise, mostly supporting factions, and getting support from them in return. None of the servers partnered with SBS are factions, hinting factions can't apply or recruit in Starboard Studios. Due to that fact, many bigger factions have went on break, disbanded or moved games. Some of these factions are Adopt Me Cult, Lotus, Clairmont Crew, Coco Pops and Pumpkin Army. Factions which have not went on break, have had trouble finding people to fight and are either slowly dying out, or are fighting their allies to stay active. Aside from bigger factions, smaller factions have little to no one to fight, and no way of recruiting new members.

Many factions are hoping SBS reverses it's changes, or adds a better recruitment so the faction community can last a few more months before dying out. (edited)
